-- Solvay sells U.S. Eco Services unit to CCMP Capital
-- By Robert-Jan Bartunek
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 01:31AM EDT
-- None



BRUSSELS, July 31 (Reuters) - Belgian chemicals group Solvay <SOLB.BR> said on Thursday that it agreed to sell its U.S. based sulphuric acid production unit Eco Services to private equity group CCMP Capital.

Solvay said the deal was based on an enterprise value of $890 million.